Technology has advanced rapidly over the last few decades, changing the way people live, work, and communicate.
Computers, smartphones, and the internet have become essential tools in everyday life. People use these devices for work,
study, and entertainment. The internet connects people from all over the world, allowing them to share ideas and experiences
instantly. The rise of social media has also transformed communication, making it easy to stay in touch with friends and family.
Overall, technology has brought many benefits, but it has also raised concerns about privacy and the impact on mental health.
